snippet.title: Interview with flutist Emily Beynon. Excerpt from the award-winning movie Exhaling Music.
snippet.description:
Interview with flutist Emily Beynon. Excerpt from the award-winning movie Exhaling Music.
Toegevoegd door Flint Juventino Beppe laatste oktober
Exhaling Music is an award-winning documentary about the life and work of composer Flint Juventino Beppe, following the special recording process for the release Flute Mystery, a recording that eventually was Grammy nominated in 2010. Director: Trond Eliassen Executive producer & copyright holder: News on Request AS © 2010 www.newson.no Published on this channel with kind permission from the producer. Composer: Flint Juventino Beppe. Music performed by Emily Beynon (flute), Catherine Beynon (harp) and Philharmonia Orchestra, conducted by Vladimir Ashkenazy and Flint Juventino Beppe. From the Grammy nominated recording Flute Mystery (2L © Lindberg Lyd AS and Composer AS). Related interviews from Exhaling Music: Vladimir Ashkenazy: http://youtu.be/skJ1CEWllJk?hd=1 Flint Juventino Beppe: http://youtu.be/XUmUyeTYojc?hd=1 Flint Juventino Beppe home page and Facebook page: http://www.fjbfingerprint.com (sheet music) http://www.facebook.com/TightropeWalking "Surrounded by secrecy, the Rognan-composer Fred Jonny Berg, 36, has captured the heart and minds of the international music scene. The self-taught composer is on first name terms with stars such as Sir James Galway and Vladimir Ashkenazy. "I never compose music", Berg says, "the tones just float around inside my head. When they get too loud, I have to breathe them out." This film is a story about a personal war, and about finally recapturing the love for music and life." - Trond Eliassen, 2010
